N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 317.14 - Reporting of obsolete labels

State Regulations

Once a year, or oftener if necessary, the operator of
each official establishment shall submit to the commissioner, in quadruplicate, a list of approved labels no longer used or a list of the documents issued by
the commissioner approving the labels involved. The approved labels shall be
identified by the approval number, the date of approval, and the name of the
product, or other designation showing the class of labeling
material. Notes
